## Summary of the Annotation/Chat Flow

1. **User selects text** in an agent message output (`onMouseUp` on chat scroll container)
2. **`handleChatTextSelection`** captures the selection, finds the parent `[data-agent-output-message]` element, and sets `annotationDraft` state with position coordinates
3. **A popup** appears at the selection position showing the selected text and a textarea for the comment
4. **User saves** the annotation via `saveAnnotation`, which stores it in the `annotations` array and persists to `localStorage`
5. **A chip** appears above the chat input showing `N selecao/selecoes` with the latest annotation preview and a clear button
6. **When sending a message**, `sendChatMessagesToAgent` calls `buildAnnotationContextMessage(annotations)` which creates a system message containing up to 8 recent annotations (text + comment), and prepends it to the payload sent to `/api/chat`
7. **The backend** (`/api/chat`) receives the messages (including the annotation system message) and passes them to `sendAgentChat`, which builds the Ollama prompt with `buildAgentContext` (separate from annotations) and the chat messages
8. **Annotations are per-chat** and stored in `localStorage` under `databridge.uiAnnotations.<chatId>`
